answers.body_markdown:
You could give the Button `input-group-btn` a width of 100%

    .input-group-btn{
     width: 100%
    }
https://jsfiddle.net/ex7rbhpw/1/&lt;br&gt;

Your Input Group (`input-group`) uses `display: table` so we just set one &quot;cell&quot; (your span with the class `input-group-btn`) to the maximum width of 100%. &lt;br&gt;
Your button will not take the full 100% because the other &quot;cells&quot; (your span-tags) have a minimum width, content or/and padding.

You can accomplish what you are looking for using `display: table` for the `input-group` container and `display: table-cell` for its child elements. Example:

    .input-group &gt; * {  
      display:table;
      width:100%;
    }
    
    .input-group &gt; * {  
      display: table-cell;
    }
    
    .input-group &gt; .form-control, .input-group &gt; .input-group-addon {
      width: 40px;
    }
    .input-group &gt; .input-group-btn, .input-group &gt; .input-group-btn &gt; button {
      width: 100%;
    }

HTH

